    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-24T02:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-24T02:54:00-05:00" n="925"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d925">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.515/20: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-24T11:00:00+03:06"
                            >July 24, 1943—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. My 66, July 14, 6 p.m. Third hundred thousand sovereigns arrived today. Saudi
                    Government has been borrowing locally and substantial portion of new shipment
                    will be used for repayments. Thus financial tension will be eased only slightly
                    if at all. Meanwhile pilgrimage draws nearer.</p>
                <p>Unless a decision is reached with regard to silver for Saudi Arabia before
                    Colonel Hoskins<note n="83" xml:id="d925fn83">Lt. Col. Harold B. Hoskins;
                        regarding the visit by Lt. Col. Hoskins to Saudi Arabia, see <ref
                            target="#pg_796">pp. 796</ref>–<ref target="#pg_821">821</ref>, <hi
                            rend="italic">passim</hi>.</note> sees King, certain of King’s advisers
                    will inevitably interpret delay in formulating silver policy as designed to <pb
                        facs="0892" n="880" xml:id="pg_880"/> influence King’s reply and such
                    interpretation may plague future relations with Saudi Arabia.</p>
                <p>Hoskins is being advised of possibility.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
